[DOCUMENT]
TITLE: GHOST Memory Management Requirements
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-MANAGEMENT
VERSION: 0.1
OPTIONS:
  MARKUP: Text
  AUTO_LEVELS: On
  NODE_IN_TOC: True

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 1. Purpose and Scope

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This document defines the top-level Memory Management capability of GHOST.

Memory Management preserves accepted interaction history as durable memory truth, creates retrieval representations, selects query-relevant memory, maintains ActiveRetrievalBrief continuity, and synthesizes runtime Memory Context for SuperPrompt composition.

Detailed atomic behavior is allocated to files 51, 52, and 53.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Memory Management Scope
STATEMENT: >>>
GHOST shall provide a Memory Management capability that records accepted input/output pairs, persists memory histories, indexes memory metadata, creates dedicated memory vectors, retrieves multiple memory candidate classes, maintains ActiveRetrievalBrief state, compresses selected evidence, and produces query-dependent Memory Context.

Memory Management shall remain separate from document Knowledge Management while participating as its logical peer after PreProcessing.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SRS-FILE-TREE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-PRODUCT-NAME
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Product and Package Naming Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
The product described by this document shall be named GHOST.

The current Python package namespace may remain ragstream in implementation paths.

Requirements shall not treat ragstream as the product identity.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-CHILD-DOCUMENTS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Memory Management Child Documents
STATEMENT: >>>
The Memory Management requirement family shall be decomposed into:
1. 51_memory_recording_and_files.sdoc;
2. 52_memory_ingestion_and_retrieval.sdoc;
3. 53_memory_merge_activebrief_blackboard.sdoc.

Each child shall own atomic requirements for its assigned capability and shall not duplicate sibling ownership.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-REQUIREMENT-NATURE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Requirement Nature
STATEMENT: >>>
This document shall define approved behavior, interfaces, boundaries, artifacts, configuration authority, and verification expectations.

It shall not be used as an implementation-status log or as permission to infer unimplemented behavior.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-CURRENT-CAPABILITIES
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Executable Memory Capabilities
STATEMENT: >>>
The current executable Memory Management scope shall include manual pair capture, memory-history files, editable metadata, SQLite indexing, ChatGPT shared-link import, memory-vector ingestion, working/episodic/semantic/Direct Recall selection, ActiveRetrievalBrief maintenance, runtime episodic compression, memory synthesis, and SuperPrompt write-back.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-NO-ANSWER-GENERATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Final Answer Generation
STATEMENT: >>>
Memory Management shall produce supporting runtime context and shall not answer the user request or own final LLM answer generation.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 2. Architectural Position and Peer Boundaries

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
The approved high-level flow is PreProcessing followed by logically independent Knowledge Management and Memory Management context paths, followed by final prompt composition.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-ARCHITECTURAL-POSITION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Memory Architectural Position
STATEMENT: >>>
Memory Management shall consume the prepared SuperPrompt after PreProcessing and shall produce a memory-specific runtime context for final prompt composition.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-KNOWLEDGE-PEER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Knowledge Management Peer Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
Memory Management and Knowledge Management shall be architectural peers.

Neither path shall require the selected output of the other path in order to execute its current selection logic.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ARCHITECTURAL-POSITION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-SERIAL-EXECUTION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Serial Execution
STATEMENT: >>>
The current controller may execute document retrieval before memory retrieval within one retrieval action.

This serial call order shall not redefine Memory Management as a child of document retrieval.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-KNOWLEDGE-PEER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-PREPROCESS-DEPENDENCY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: PreProcessing Dependency
STATEMENT: >>>
Memory retrieval shall consume the effective retrieval query and ActiveBrief routing permissions prepared by 30_preprocessing_prompt_functions.sdoc.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ARCHITECTURAL-POSITION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-DOCUMENT-INDEPENDENCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Document Candidate Independence
STATEMENT: >>>
Memory scoring, deterministic lookups, compression, and synthesis shall not depend on document candidate scores, document A3 labels, document A4 classes, or S_CTX_MD.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-KNOWLEDGE-PEER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-NO-DOCUMENT-MUTATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Document Artifact Mutation
STATEMENT: >>>
Memory Management shall not mutate document base_context_chunks, document stage views, document final_selection_ids, or S_CTX_MD.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-DOCUMENT-INDEPENDENCE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-A3-A4-BOUNDARY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Document A3 and A4 Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
Current A3 and A4 shall remain document-evidence stages.

Memory semantic chunks shall not be described as passing through document A3 or A4 in the current architecture.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-DOCUMENT-INDEPENDENCE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-FINAL-COMPOSITION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Final Prompt Composition Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
Final prompt composition shall render synthesized memory_context_text as supporting background context.

Memory Management shall not own the final ordering of every SuperPrompt section or provider submission.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ARCHITECTURAL-POSITION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-AGENT-STACK-BOUNDARY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Agent Stack Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
ActiveBrief summarization and Memory Context synthesis shall use the neutral Agent Stack defined in 20_agent_stack.sdoc.

This Memory requirement family shall own the concrete memory payloads, decisions, safeguards, and state write-back.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-GUI-BOUNDARY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: GUI Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
The GUI may trigger, display, or edit memory operations, but durable-memory semantics and retrieval policy shall remain owned by server-side memory components.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 3. Functional Decomposition and Lifecycle

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
Memory Management combines durable recording, derivative ingestion, query-time retrieval, continuity maintenance, and runtime synthesis without replacing durable memory truth.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-RECORDING-CAPABILITY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Memory Recording Capability
STATEMENT: >>>
Memory Recording shall create and maintain MemoryRecord objects, active history identity, append-only stable-body files, editable metadata files, and a SQLite metadata mirror.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-FILE-CAPABILITY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Memory File Lifecycle Capability
STATEMENT: >>>
Memory file operations shall list, create, load, rename, and delete memory histories using stable file_id identity and mutable filenames.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-IMPORT-CAPABILITY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Conversation Import Capability
STATEMENT: >>>
The current import capability shall convert one public ChatGPT shared-link conversation into ordinary MemoryRecord objects and persist it as an ordinary memory history.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-INGESTION-CAPABILITY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Memory Ingestion Capability
STATEMENT: >>>
Memory Ingestion shall derive record-handle, question, and answer vector entries from durable MemoryRecord content and store them in the dedicated memory vector store.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-RETRIEVAL-CAPABILITY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Memory Retrieval Capability
STATEMENT: >>>
Memory Retrieval shall combine semantic-vector results with deterministic SQLite/.ragmem lookups into a structured MemoryContextPack.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-ACTIVEBRIEF-CAPABILITY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: ActiveRetrievalBrief Capability
STATEMENT: >>>
ActiveRetrievalBrief maintenance shall create or update a compact query-independent conversation brief when a MemoryRecord is captured and shall preserve contributor traceability.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-COMPRESSION-CAPABILITY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Runtime Compression Capability
STATEMENT: >>>
Runtime compression shall reduce selected episodic Q/A evidence against the effective query without modifying durable MemoryRecord text.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-SYNTHESIS-CAPABILITY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Memory Context Synthesis Capability
STATEMENT: >>>
Memory synthesis shall produce one compact query-relevant memory_context string from the current configured evidence inputs.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-CAPTURE-SEQUENCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Capture Sequence
STATEMENT: >>>
The current pair-capture sequence shall synchronize editable GUI metadata, create a new MemoryRecord, build its ActiveRetrievalBrief, append the stable body to .ragmem, rewrite .ragmeta.json, refresh SQLite, and then optionally schedule vector ingestion.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-RECORDING-CAPABILITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-RETRIEVAL-SEQUENCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Retrieval Sequence
STATEMENT: >>>
The current memory retrieval sequence shall build a query, run semantic retrieval and deterministic lookups, score and merge candidates, compress episodic candidates, synthesize Memory Context, build diagnostics, and write memory artifacts into SuperPrompt.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-RETRIEVAL-CAPABILITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-DURABLE-BEFORE-DERIVATIVE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Durable Save Before Vector Ingestion
STATEMENT: >>>
A MemoryRecord shall be durably saved before its vector ingestion is scheduled.

Failure to schedule or complete vector ingestion shall not invalidate the already saved MemoryRecord truth.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-CAPTURE-SEQUENCE

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 4. Authority and Data Truth Model

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
The memory subsystem deliberately separates authoritative stable content, current editable metadata, lookup indexes, vector derivatives, and run-local context.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-TRUTH-MODEL
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Memory Truth Model
STATEMENT: >>>
Full accepted input/output MemoryRecord content in .ragmem shall remain the durable memory-body authority.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-STABLE-BODY-AUTHORITY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Stable Body Authority
STATEMENT: >>>
Stable identity, timestamps, input/output text, source, hashes, and stored ActiveRetrievalBrief fields shall be loaded from .ragmem.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-TRUTH-MODEL

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-METADATA-AUTHORITY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Editable Metadata Authority
STATEMENT: >>>
Current editable tags, retrieval source mode, Direct Recall Key, user keywords, automatic keywords, project name, and embedded-file snapshot shall be represented in .ragmeta.json and overlaid onto loaded MemoryRecords.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-TRUTH-MODEL

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-SQLITE-MIRROR
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: SQLite Mirror Status
STATEMENT: >>>
memory_index.sqlite3 shall mirror file-level and record-level metadata for deterministic lookup and shall not replace .ragmem as full Q/A truth.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-TRUTH-MODEL

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-VECTOR-DERIVATIVE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Vector Store Derivative Status
STATEMENT: >>>
Memory vectors, embedded documents, vector metadata, and similarity results shall be derivative retrieval aids and shall not replace MemoryRecord truth.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-TRUTH-MODEL

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-PACK-RUNTIME-ONLY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: MemoryContextPack Runtime Status
STATEMENT: >>>
MemoryContextPack shall be run-local retrieval output and shall not be persisted as durable memory truth.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-TRUTH-MODEL

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-CONTEXT-RUNTIME-ONLY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Synthesized Memory Context Status
STATEMENT: >>>
memory_context_text shall be query-dependent runtime context and shall not be written back into .ragmem, .ragmeta.json, SQLite, or the memory vector store.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-TRUTH-MODEL

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-PENDING-BUFFER-RUNTIME
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Pending Topic Buffer Status
STATEMENT: >>>
pending_activebrief_topic_buffer shall remain RAM-only and shall not be persisted in .ragmem, .ragmeta.json, SQLite, or vectors.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-TRUTH-MODEL

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-ONE-ACTIVE-HISTORY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Single Active Memory History
STATEMENT: >>>
One MemoryManager instance shall own one active memory history and its in-memory record list at a time.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-TRUTH-MODEL

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-IDENTITY-SEPARATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: File Identity and Filename Separation
STATEMENT: >>>
file_id shall be the stable memory-history identity.

filename_ragmem and filename_meta shall be mutable path/display attributes and shall not become the identity key.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-TRUTH-MODEL

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-PARENT-TRACE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Record Parent Trace
STATEMENT: >>>
A MemoryRecord may carry parent_id to preserve a chain relationship without changing record_id identity.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-TRUTH-MODEL

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 5. Runtime Candidate and Context Model

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
Memory retrieval preserves several candidate roles because recent continuity, semantic similarity, explicit priority, and exact recall are not equivalent selection mechanisms.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-WORKING-ROLE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Working Memory Candidate Role
STATEMENT: >>>
Working memory shall represent the latest configured non-excluded records from the active memory history through deterministic SQLite lookup.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-EPISODIC-ROLE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Episodic Candidate Role
STATEMENT: >>>
Episodic memory shall represent parent MemoryRecords selected from semantic parent scoring and the configured Gold priority lookup.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-SEMANTIC-ROLE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Semantic Chunk Role
STATEMENT: >>>
Semantic memory chunks shall represent selected question or answer vector hits with record traceability, semantic score, and optional recency contribution.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-DIRECT-ROLE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Direct Recall Candidate Role
STATEMENT: >>>
Direct Recall shall represent at most one exact-key lookup result across memory histories, subject to tag exclusion and configured enablement.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-ACTIVEBRIEF-ROLE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: ActiveRetrievalBrief Role
STATEMENT: >>>
ActiveRetrievalBrief shall provide query-independent working-conversation orientation and shall remain distinct from query-dependent Memory Context.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-SYNTHESIZED-ROLE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Synthesized Memory Context Role
STATEMENT: >>>
Synthesized Memory Context shall be the memory artifact rendered in the normal SuperPrompt supporting-context preview.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-CURRENT-SYNTHESIS-INPUTS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Synthesis Input Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
The current MemoryMergeSynthesizer shall receive compressed episodic candidates and semantic memory chunks.

Working-memory candidates and Direct Recall shall remain present in MemoryContextPack but are not currently passed into the synthesizer evidence payload.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-SYNTHESIZED-ROLE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-NO-RAW-PACK-DEFAULT-RENDER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Raw Pack Rendering by Default
STATEMENT: >>>
The normal SuperPrompt preview shall render memory_context_text and shall not render the raw MemoryContextPack candidate dump by default.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-SYNTHESIZED-ROLE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-ACTIVEBRIEF-ANTI-DUP
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: ActiveBrief Anti-Duplication Reference
STATEMENT: >>>
Memory synthesis shall use ActiveRetrievalBrief as orientation and anti-duplication reference rather than as substitute memory evidence.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ACTIVEBRIEF-ROLE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-CURRENT-OVERLAP-SCOPE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Overlap Handling Scope
STATEMENT: >>>
The current memory synthesizer may combine duplicate episodic and semantic memory evidence within the memory path.

Cross-path overlap removal between document context and memory context is not implemented.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-SYNTHESIZED-ROLE

[[/SECTION]]

