[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 7. Configuration Governance

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
Memory behavior combines current versioned JSON settings with a small number of current Python defaults and startup constants.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-CONFIG-ROOT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Runtime Configuration Source
STATEMENT: >>>
Current memory retrieval, compression, ActiveBrief, and synthesis settings shall be read from ragstream/config/runtime_config.json where the implementation currently consumes them.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-CONFIG-SECTIONS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Memory Configuration Sections
STATEMENT: >>>
The current JSON configuration shall contain memory_retrieval, memory_compression, memory_merge_synthesizer, and memory_active_retrieval_brief sections.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-CONFIG-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-CONFIG-VALIDATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Configuration Validation Direction
STATEMENT: >>>
Operational limits, thresholds, weights, model identifiers, enable switches, and token budgets shall be validated before use when migrated into the versioned JSON contract.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-CONFIG-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-TUNABLES-JSON-DIRECTION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Tunable Parameter JSON Direction
STATEMENT: >>>
Tunable Memory Management parameters shall progressively move to versioned JSON configuration rather than remain scattered as Python literals.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-CONFIG-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-CURRENT-PYTHON-DEFAULTS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Python Defaults
STATEMENT: >>>
A value that remains defined only in Python shall be documented as a current implementation default and shall not be reported as JSON-controlled.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-CONFIG-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-DEFINED-NOT-CONSUMED
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Defined but Unconsumed Settings
STATEMENT: >>>
A configuration field present in runtime_config.json shall not be claimed as enforced unless the current execution path reads and applies that field.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-CONFIG-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-STARTUP-EMBEDDER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Memory Vector Embedder
STATEMENT: >>>
Current Streamlit startup shall initialize MemoryVectorStore with OpenAI text-embedding-3-large and collection name memory_vectors.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-CONFIG-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-REDUCER-EMBEDDER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Reduction Embedder
STATEMENT: >>>
Current ActiveBrief reduction, relevance gating, and episodic query compression shall use the configured embedding model whose current JSON baseline is text-embedding-3-small.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-CONFIG-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-AGENT-VERSIONS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Versioned Memory Agent Selection
STATEMENT: >>>
ActiveBrief init, ActiveBrief update, and Memory Context synthesis shall resolve explicit configured agent identifiers and versions.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-CONFIG-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-CONFIG-OBSERVABILITY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Effective Configuration Observability
STATEMENT: >>>
Diagnostics shall identify the effective memory selection and synthesis policy sufficiently to reproduce a run without exposing secrets.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-CONFIG-ROOT

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 8. Error Handling, Security, and Quality Boundaries

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
Durable memory truth must remain intact when derivative or runtime processing fails.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-FAILURE-ISOLATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Derivative Failure Isolation
STATEMENT: >>>
Vector-ingestion, retrieval, compression, or synthesis failure shall not rewrite or corrupt existing durable .ragmem content.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-NO-FABRICATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Fabricated Memory
STATEMENT: >>>
Memory components shall not invent MemoryRecords, source text, candidate bodies, tags, keys, scores, or synthesized facts when inputs are missing or processing fails.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-EMPTY-PACK
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Explicit Empty Retrieval Pack
STATEMENT: >>>
When no active history or no query is available, Memory Retrieval shall write an explicit empty MemoryContextPack with a diagnostic reason rather than fabricate context.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-SYNTHESIS-FAILURE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Synthesis Failure Integrity
STATEMENT: >>>
A Memory Context synthesis failure shall produce empty memory_context and failure diagnostics rather than an invented fallback context.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-SECRET-BOUNDARY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Credential Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
Provider credentials shall remain outside .ragmem, .ragmeta.json, SQLite memory metadata, vector metadata, and agent JSON files.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-PUBLIC-LOG-BOUNDARY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Public Logging Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
Public logs shall report concise statuses and identifiers and shall not expose complete prompts, memory bodies, ActiveBrief text, vector values, or model payloads by default.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-DEVELOPER-LOG-BOUNDARY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Developer Logging Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
Detailed memory payloads and diagnostics shall remain in explicitly enabled confidential developer logging paths.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-DETERMINISTIC-TESTABILITY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Deterministic Component Testability
STATEMENT: >>>
Filename sanitation, metadata normalization, SQLite lookups, chunk identity, score conversion, recency decay, candidate merging, and empty-state behavior shall be independently testable without an LLM call.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-LLM-TESTABILITY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: LLM Boundary Testability
STATEMENT: >>>
ActiveBrief and Memory Context LLM calls shall be replaceable with controlled AgentFactory and LLMClient test doubles.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-PROVENANCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Memory Provenance
STATEMENT: >>>
Every vector hit, episodic candidate, semantic chunk, Direct Recall result, and ActiveBrief contributor shall remain traceable to record_id and, where applicable, file_id.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 9. Sibling Ownership and Future Boundary

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This section prevents the top-level document from absorbing child details or claiming future concepts as current behavior.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-REC-FILE-REFERENCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Recording and File Ownership
STATEMENT: >>>
Detailed MemoryRecord, .ragmem, .ragmeta.json, SQLite, capture, file lifecycle, and import requirements shall be owned by 51_memory_recording_and_files.sdoc.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-INGEST-RETRIEVE-REFERENCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Ingestion and Retrieval Ownership
STATEMENT: >>>
Detailed vector-entry, memory-store, ingestion, deterministic lookup, semantic scoring, candidate selection, and MemoryContextPack requirements shall be owned by 52_memory_ingestion_and_retrieval.sdoc.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-MERGE-REFERENCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: ActiveBrief and Merge Ownership
STATEMENT: >>>
Detailed sentence reduction, ActiveBrief relevance routing, pending-topic handling, runtime compression, and Memory Context synthesis requirements shall be owned by 53_memory_merge_activebrief_blackboard.sdoc.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-PREPROCESS-REFERENCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: PreProcessing Ownership Reference
STATEMENT: >>>
Prompt parsing, ActiveBrief relation classification, and memory-context permission policy shall remain owned by 30_preprocessing_prompt_functions.sdoc.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-KM-REFERENCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Knowledge Management Ownership Reference
STATEMENT: >>>
Document ingestion, document retrieval/reranking, document A3, and document A4 shall remain owned by files 40–43.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-PROMPT-COMPOSITION-REFERENCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Prompt Composition Ownership Reference
STATEMENT: >>>
Final LLM-ready prompt assembly shall remain outside files 50–53.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-BLACKBOARD-NOT-CURRENT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Blackboard Current Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
No current Blackboard coordinator, shared Blackboard state model, or Blackboard background-agent workflow shall be claimed as implemented by files 50–53.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-KNOWLEDGE-GRAPH-NOT-CURRENT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Knowledge Graph Current Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
Knowledge-graph memory representation or graph-based retrieval shall not be claimed as current Memory Management behavior.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-CROSS-OVERLAP-NOT-CURRENT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Cross-Context Deduplication Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
Automatic overlap detection and removal between final document context and final memory context shall remain outside the current implementation baseline.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-BACKGROUND-AGENTS-NOT-CURRENT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Background Agent Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
Background agents for requirement-code synchronization, autonomous memory maintenance, or unattended context repair shall not be claimed as current Memory Management behavior.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-CODE-TRACEABILITY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Code Traceability Direction
STATEMENT: >>>
Memory implementation units shall be traceable to the deepest applicable UID in files 51–53 rather than only to the top-level Memory Management root.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-CHANGE-SYNC
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Requirement-Code Synchronization
STATEMENT: >>>
An approved change to memory truth, persistence, indexing, retrieval policy, score semantics, runtime artifacts, or observable output shall update requirements, architecture, implementation traceability, and verification together.

Pure internal refactoring that preserves approved behavior shall not require artificial requirement changes.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 10. Acceptance Criteria

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
These criteria validate the top-level Memory Management architecture without duplicating child-level tests.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-AC-HIERARCHY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Memory Hierarchy
STATEMENT: >>>
The approved requirements set shall show durable recording, derivative ingestion/retrieval, ActiveBrief/compression/synthesis, and final prompt handoff as separate owned responsibilities.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-AC-PEER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Knowledge Peer Independence
STATEMENT: >>>
Given a prepared SuperPrompt and active memory history, Memory Management shall execute without requiring document retrieval or A3/A4 results.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-KNOWLEDGE-PEER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-AC-TRUTH
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Durable Truth Separation
STATEMENT: >>>
A vector-store deletion or empty retrieval run shall not delete or rewrite the corresponding .ragmem MemoryRecord body.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-TRUTH-MODEL

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-AC-METADATA
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Metadata Overlay
STATEMENT: >>>
Loading a history shall reconstruct stable bodies from .ragmem and overlay current editable metadata from .ragmeta.json.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-METADATA-AUTHORITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-AC-PACK
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Candidate Pack Separation
STATEMENT: >>>
One retrieval run shall preserve working, episodic, semantic, Direct Recall, synthesis, selection-diagnostic, and token-report fields as distinguishable MemoryContextPack artifacts.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-PACK-RUNTIME-ONLY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-AC-CURRENT-SYNTHESIS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Current Synthesis Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
The current synthesizer input shall contain episodic and semantic evidence, while working and Direct Recall candidates remain separately inspectable in the pack.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-CURRENT-SYNTHESIS-INPUTS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-AC-EMPTY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Empty Memory Context
STATEMENT: >>>
Given no usable memory evidence, the run shall produce an empty memory_context string and shall not fabricate a memory summary.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-NO-FABRICATION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-AC-CONFIG
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Configuration Truth
STATEMENT: >>>
A setting shall be reported as effective only when the current execution path reads and applies it.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-DEFINED-NOT-CONSUMED

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-AC-PROVENANCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Candidate Provenance
STATEMENT: >>>
Every selected memory candidate shall expose sufficient file_id/record_id or vector_id/record_id linkage to identify its durable parent.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-PROVENANCE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-AC-NO-FUTURE-LEAK
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: No Future Feature Leakage
STATEMENT: >>>
The current memory requirements shall not claim implemented Blackboard coordination, knowledge-graph retrieval, cross-path context deduplication, or background synchronization agents.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-BLACKBOARD-NOT-CURRENT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEMORY-AC-SYNC
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Requirement-Code Consistency
STATEMENT: >>>
A release baseline shall not be accepted when memory authority, persistence, candidate roles, synthesis inputs, configuration authority, or SuperPrompt artifact semantics contradict this requirement family.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEMORY-CHANGE-SYNC

